{
    "componentChunkName": "component---src-templates-template-js",
    "path": "/inheritance/casting",
    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The Java type system is made up of two kinds of types:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>primitives</li>\n<li>references</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/aa440/PrimitiveReference.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 41.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"PrimitiveReference\"\n        title=\"PrimitiveReference\"\n        src=\"/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/5a190/PrimitiveReference.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/772e8/PrimitiveReference.png 200w,\n/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/e17e5/PrimitiveReference.png 400w,\n/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/5a190/PrimitiveReference.png 800w,\n/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/c1b63/PrimitiveReference.png 1200w,\n/static/5b6777b2ca21a4bb89f0147041718d11/aa440/PrimitiveReference.png 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"casting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#casting\" aria-label=\"casting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Casting</h2>\n<p>Casting (conversion) of primitives and references are <strong>two different things</strong></p>\n<p>Primitive casting:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Widening (implicit, automatic) casting</li>\n<li>Narrowing (explicit) casting</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"widening-primitive-casting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#widening-primitive-casting\" aria-label=\"widening primitive casting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Widening primitive casting</h2>\n<p>1 byte -> 2 bytes -> 4 bytes -> 8 bytes</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 550px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0fcad518a5f85e8a5e4cda63728eed0e/d7854/widening-type-conversion.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"widening\"\n        title=\"widening\"\n        src=\"/static/0fcad518a5f85e8a5e4cda63728eed0e/d7854/widening-type-conversion.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0fcad518a5f85e8a5e4cda63728eed0e/e07e9/widening-type-conversion.jpg 200w,\n/static/0fcad518a5f85e8a5e4cda63728eed0e/066f9/widening-type-conversion.jpg 400w,\n/static/0fcad518a5f85e8a5e4cda63728eed0e/d7854/widening-type-conversion.jpg 550w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">long</span> l <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> i<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\t<span class=\"token comment\">//no explicit type casting required</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">float</span> f <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> l<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\t<span class=\"token comment\">//no explicit type casting required</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Int value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Long value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>l<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Float value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>f<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ini\"><pre class=\"language-ini\"><code class=\"language-ini\">Int value 100\nLong value 100\nFloat value 100.0</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"narrowing-primitive-casting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#narrowing-primitive-casting\" aria-label=\"narrowing primitive casting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Narrowing primitive casting</h2>\n<p>8 bytes -> 4 bytes -> 2 bytes -> 1 bytes</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 550px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/18ed3a3af4fd5455fa6672df2fe55009/d7854/narrowing-type-conversion.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 26%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"narrowing type conversion\"\n        title=\"narrowing type conversion\"\n        src=\"/static/18ed3a3af4fd5455fa6672df2fe55009/d7854/narrowing-type-conversion.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/18ed3a3af4fd5455fa6672df2fe55009/e07e9/narrowing-type-conversion.jpg 200w,\n/static/18ed3a3af4fd5455fa6672df2fe55009/066f9/narrowing-type-conversion.jpg 400w,\n/static/18ed3a3af4fd5455fa6672df2fe55009/d7854/narrowing-type-conversion.jpg 550w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> d <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">100.04</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">long</span> l <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">long</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">//explicit type casting required</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>l<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\t<span class=\"token comment\">//explicit type casting required</span>\n\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Double value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Long value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>l<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Int value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ini\"><pre class=\"language-ini\"><code class=\"language-ini\">Double value 100.04\nLong value 100\nInt value 100</code></pre></div>\n<p>Narrowing primitive casting may have unpredictable consequences:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">double</span> d <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">108374658347560.04</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">long</span> l <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">long</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">//explicit type casting required</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> i <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>l<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\t<span class=\"token comment\">//explicit type casting required</span>\n\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Double value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>d<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Long value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>l<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Int value \"</span><span class=\"token operator\">+</span>i<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ini\"><pre class=\"language-ini\"><code class=\"language-ini\">Double value 1.0837465834756005E14\nLong value 108374658347560\nInt value -251432408</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"reference-casting\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#reference-casting\" aria-label=\"reference casting permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Reference casting</h2>\n<p>Reference variables only refer to objects but do not contain the objects themselves.</p>\n<p>Casting a reference variable doesn’t touch the object it refers to, it only labels this object in another way, expanding or narrowing opportunities to work with it.</p>\n<p><strong>Upcasting</strong> narrows the list of methods and properties available to the object.</p>\n<p><strong>Downcasting</strong> may extend the list of methods and properties available to the object.</p>\n<h2 id=\"upcasting-reference-variables\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#upcasting-reference-variables\" aria-label=\"upcasting reference variables permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Upcasting reference variables</h2>\n<p>Casting from a subclass to a superclass is called <strong>upcasting</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">eat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token comment\">// ... </span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">meow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">// ... </span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span> cat <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> animal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> cat<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">//implicit</span>\nanimal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> cat<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">//explicit: not needed in upcasting</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We’ve restricted the number of methods available to Cat instance but haven’t changed the instance itself.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span> cat <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> animal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> cat<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> \n\ncat<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">meow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\t\t<span class=\"token comment\">// ok</span>\nanimal<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">meow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  <span class=\"token comment\">// not ok: method meow() is undefined for the type Animal</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"downcasting-reference-variables\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#downcasting-reference-variables\" aria-label=\"downcasting reference variables permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Downcasting reference variables</h2>\n<p>Casting from a a superclass to a subclass is called <strong>downcasting</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">eat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token comment\">// ... </span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">meow</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token comment\">// ... </span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">Animal</span> animal <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span> cat <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Cat</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> animal<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"exercise\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#exercise\" aria-label=\"exercise permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Exercise</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Write class A:\n<ul>\n<li>Add methodA()</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Write class B:\n<ul>\n<li>It extends A</li>\n<li>Add methodB()</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Try upcasting and downcasting</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- ## Solution\n\n```java\nclass A {\n    public void methodA(){ System.out.println(\"Does A\"); }\n}\n\nclass B extends A {\n    public void methodB(){ System.out.println(\"Does b\"); }\n}\n\npublic class Runner {\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        A a = new A();\n        a.methodA();\n    \n        B b = new B();\n        b.methodA();\n        b.methodB();\n\n        A a2 = new B();\n        a2.methodA();\n\n        A a3 = new B(); //we don't have access to methodB()\n        a3.methodA();\n        B b2 = (B) a3;\n        b2.methodB(); //downcasting\n\n        B b3 = (B) new A();\n        b3.methodA();\n        b3.methodB();\t//runtime error\n    }\n}\n``` -->\n<h2 id=\"casting-with-interfaces\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#casting-with-interfaces\" aria-label=\"casting with interfaces permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Casting with Interfaces</h2>\n<p>Consider the scenario below:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 215px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2dd277c0250335c43b9a73833545c480/2eb24/cast-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 88.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"CAST1\"\n        title=\"CAST1\"\n        src=\"/static/2dd277c0250335c43b9a73833545c480/2eb24/cast-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2dd277c0250335c43b9a73833545c480/772e8/cast-1.png 200w,\n/static/2dd277c0250335c43b9a73833545c480/2eb24/cast-1.png 215w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 215px) 100vw, 215px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">interface</span> C1 <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">interface</span> C2 <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">B</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> C1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> C2 <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Given this hierarchy, all the following statements are valid:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">B</span> b <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">B</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> a\t<span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">A</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">C1</span> c1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>C1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">C2</span> c2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>C2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">C1</span> c11 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>C1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">A</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now, supposed that both <code class=\"language-text\">A</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">B</code> implement the method <code class=\"language-text\">whoAmI()</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"I am A.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">B</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">extends</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> C1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> C2 <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token annotation punctuation\">@Override</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"I am B.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In our <code class=\"language-text\">main()</code> we write the following instructions:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">B</span> b <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">B</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">A</span> a\t<span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">A</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">C1</span> c1 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>C1<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">C2</span> c2 <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>C2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>b<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nc1<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// compile error: not accessible through C1</span>\nc2<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// compile error: not accessible through C2</span>\n\nb<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// which version of the method will be invoked?</span>\na<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">whoAmI</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// which version of the method will be invoked?</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Which version of <code class=\"language-text\">whoAmI()</code> is going to be called in each line?</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">A.whoAmI()</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">B.whoAmI()</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The answer is <strong>always the overrided one</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ini\"><pre class=\"language-ini\"><code class=\"language-ini\">I am B.\nI am B.</code></pre></div>\n<p>Remember that both <code class=\"language-text\">b</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">a</code> point to the same object of type <code class=\"language-text\">B</code>, which has the following methods:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">whoAmI()</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">anotherMethod()</code></li>\n<li>the difference between variables <code class=\"language-text\">a</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">b</code> is only in the methods that are accessible</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Through <code class=\"language-text\">b</code> we have access to the methods (of the object of type <code class=\"language-text\">B</code>)</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">whoAmI()</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">anotherMethod()</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Through <code class=\"language-text\">a</code> we have access only to the method (of the object of type <code class=\"language-text\">B</code>)</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">whoAmI()</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"exercise-1\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#exercise-1\" aria-label=\"exercise 1 permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Exercise</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Create an interface <code class=\"language-text\">Sortable</code>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">isBiggerThan((Sortable) obj)</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Create class <code class=\"language-text\">Building implements Sortable</code>\n<ul>\n<li>height + getter/setter</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Create class <code class=\"language-text\">Land implements Sortable</code>\n<ul>\n<li>width, length + getters/setters</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Create a class <code class=\"language-text\">Runner</code> with a <code class=\"language-text\">main</code> method that:\n<ul>\n<li>Creates three <code class=\"language-text\">Building</code> objects with heights 20, 80, and 60 meters</li>\n<li>Creates three <code class=\"language-text\">Land</code> objects of the sizes 20x30, 10x5, and 25x25 square meters</li>\n<li>Find the tallest building</li>\n<li>Find the largest land</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<!-- ## Solution\n\n```java\npublic interface Sortable {\n\tint isBiggerThan(Sortable obj);\n}\n```\n\n```java\npublic class Building implements Sortable {\n\t\n\tprivate int height = 0;\n\n\tpublic int getHeight() {\n\t\treturn height;\n\t}\n\n\tpublic void setHeight(int height) {\n\t\tthis.height = height;\n\t}\n\n\t@Override\n\tpublic int isBiggerThan(Sortable obj) {\n\t\tBuilding otherBuilding = (Building) obj;\n\t\tif (this.getHeight() > otherBuilding.getHeight())\n\t\t\treturn 1;\n\t\telse\n\t\t\treturn 0;\n\t}\n\n\tpublic Building(int height) {\n\t\tsuper();\n\t\tthis.height = height;\n\t}\n\n}\n```\n\n```java\npublic class Land implements Sortable {\n\tprivate int width = 0;\n\tprivate int length = 0;\n\n\tpublic int getWidth() { return width; \t}\n\n\tpublic void setWidth(int width) { this.width = width; \t}\n\n\tpublic int getLength() { return length; }\n\n\tpublic void setLength(int length) { this.length = length; }\n\t\n\tpublic int getArea() { return this.getLength() * this.getWidth(); }\n\n\t@Override\n\tpublic int isBiggerThan(Sortable obj) {\n\t\tLand otherLand = (Land) obj;\n\t\tif (this.getArea() > otherLand.getArea())\n\t\t\treturn 1;\n\t\telse\n\t\t\treturn 0;\n\t}\n\n\tpublic Land(int width, int length) {\n\t\tsuper();\n\t\tthis.width = width;\n\t\tthis.length = length;\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n```java\npublic class Runner {\n\n\tpublic static void main(String[] args) {\n\t\tBuilding b1 = new Building(20);\n\t\tBuilding b2 = new Building(80);\n\t\tBuilding b3 = new Building(60);\n\t\tBuilding tallestBuilding = b1;\n\t\tif (b2.isBiggerThan(tallestBuilding) > 0)\n\t\t\ttallestBuilding = b2;\n\t\tif (b3.isBiggerThan(tallestBuilding) > 0)\n\t\t\ttallestBuilding = b3;\n\t\tSystem.out.println(\"The tallest building is \"+tallestBuilding.getHeight() + \" m high\");\n\t\t\n\t\tLand l1 = new Land(20, 30);\n\t\tLand l2 = new Land(10, 5);\n\t\tLand l3 = new Land(25, 25);\n\t\tLand biggestLand = l1;\n\t\tif (l2.isBiggerThan(biggestLand) > 0)\n\t\t\tbiggestLand = l2;\n\t\tif (l3.isBiggerThan(biggestLand) > 0)\n\t\t\tbiggestLand = l3;\n\t\tSystem.out.println(\"The biggest land is \" + biggestLand.getLength()+\"x\"+biggestLand.getWidth());;\n\t}\n}\n``` -->","frontmatter":{"slug":"/inheritance/casting","title":"Casting","course":"Programming Project 2021/22","previous":"/inheritance/object","next":"/generics/introduction","chapter":6,"section":9,"module":"Inheritance","banner":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/inheritance/casting"}},
